The Left Hand of Darkness - Ursula K. Le Guin - 2010 Ace Books Paperback

Regular price $8.00

Shipping calculated at checkout.

Condition: Acceptable. Please see the images for more details.

Publisher blurb: "Genly Ai is an ethnologist observing the people of the planet Gethen, a world perpetually in winter. The people there are androgynous, normally neuter, but they can become male ot female at the peak of their sexual cycle. They seem to Genly Ai alien, unsophisticated and confusing. But he is drawn into the complex politics of the planet and, during a long, tortuous journey across the ice with a politician who has fallen from favour and has been outcast, he loses his professional detachment and reaches a painful understanding of the true nature of Gethenians and, in a moving and memorable sequence, even finds love..."
